  "prompt": "What is reliance jio?",
  "response": "Reliance Jio is a telecommunications company in India, launched in September 2016 by Mukesh Ambani, chairman of Reliance Industries. Key features include:\n\n1. Mobile Network\n- 4G LTE and 5G network\n- Provides mobile and broadband services\n- Nationwide coverage across India\n\n2. Business Model\n- Offered free voice calls and very low-cost data plans\n- Disrupted telecom market with aggressive pricing\n- Quickly gained a large subscriber base\n\n3. Digital Services\n- Jio Phone (affordable feature and smartphone devices)\n- JioTV\n- JioSaavn (music streaming)\n- JioMart (e-commerce platform)\n- Other digital services and applications\n\n4. Impact\n- Transformed Indian telecom industry\n- Increased internet penetration\n- Forced competitors to lower prices\n- Promoted digital connectivity in India\n\n5. Ownership\n- Subsidiary of Reliance Industries\n- Part of Mukesh Ambani's digital ecosystem\n\nJio has become one of the largest telecom operators in India, with millions of subscribers and significant market share.",
